            "text": "Here's the latest news about Google:\n\n**AI and New Products:**\n\n*   **Gemma 4:** Google has unveiled Gemma 4, expanding its lineup of lightweight open models for developers. The Gemma 4 model offers capabilities such as advanced reasoning, agentic workflows, and coding, and supports over 140 languages.\n*   **Google Vids:** Google's new Vids update makes AI video creation simple and free, allowing users to generate short video clips from text prompts. You can create, edit, and share videos at no cost in Google Vids.\n*   **AI-Powered Gmail Inbox:** Google has launched a new AI-powered Gmail inbox experience for premium users, currently in beta in the US. This feature, built on Gemini capabilities, can filter through junk, summarize an inbox, and even help users write emails.\n*   **Lyria 3 Pro:** Google Labs is offering Lyria 3 Pro to create longer tracks in more Google products.\n\n**Google Business and Legal Matters:**\n\n*   **Turkey Investigation:** Turkey has launched an investigation into Google over advertising and billing practices.\n*   **Indonesia Summons:** Indonesia has issued fresh summons for Google and Meta over a teen social media ban. The tech giants allegedly ignored a new ban on social media for users under 16.\n*   **Privacy Lawsuit:** Google will pay $68 million to settle allegations it eavesdropped on users. A class-action lawsuit alleged that Google's voice assistant illegally recorded and shared private conversations with advertisers.\n*   **App Store Commissions:** Google settled with Epic Games with an offer to lower its app store commissions.\n\n**Google Personnel:**\n\n*   **Sundar Pichai to speak at Stanford:** Google and Alphabet CEO Sundar Pichai is \"returning\" to Stanford University after 31 years to deliver the 2026 commencement address.\n*   **Employee Leaves Google:** A Bengaluru tech professional, Harshit Sharma, has quit his Google job for a year-long 'experiment' to explore life and passions.\n\n**Other News:**\n\n*   **Acquisition:** Google has announced its biggest acquisition in its 28-year history, acquiring a business making security tools to protect information stored.\n*   **London HQ:** Google is starting its long-awaited move into Platform 37 London HQ this summer and has christened its new London headquarters 'Platform 37'.\n*   **Google Maps Overhaul:** Google Maps is set for a huge overhaul.\n*   **AI for Health:** Google is using AI to improve health for everyone.\n*   **Protecting Forests:** Google Earth is creating a new satellite imagery map to help protect Brazil's forests.\n"
          }
        ],
